4.  About the Author


The part where I get to talk about me, oh what fun...

I'm a 23 year old postgraduate in the Robotics Group at the University of
Newcastle upon Tyne, working on force feedback control systems.  In my 
spare time I hitch-hike on the information traffic jam, watch Babylon 5, listen
to a wide variety of music, especially the @{"Spice Girls" link "spice" 0}, fly around virtual 
skies in a variety of simulated warplanes on my quite nice @{"PC" link "PC" 0}, and mess 
around with pretty much anything on my @{"Amiga" link "Amiga" 0}, which is even nicer :-)

What else?  I read a lot, I build model kits, I go for long walks in the
beautiful Northumbrian and Cumbrian countryside, I do a bit of cycling and
many other interesting things...


Any e-mail about QuickCode should be sent to:

                     quickcode@tornado.pair.com
                       
Or if you feel like taking a walk on the web, point your browser at:

                    http://www.tornado.pair.com/
                   
where you'll find, amongst other things, my Amiga page.  The latest version
of QuickCode will always be available from this page, along with other
little things I've hacked together, so it might be worth a visit...


