@node "spice" "Spice Girls :-)"
Girl Power, Girls with Attitude, Spice is Nice, etc. etc...


Yes, I'm 23.  Yes, I'm a (presumably) intelligent postgraduate.  And yes, 
I like the Spice Girls.  So what?  The aren't just for little kiddies you 
know, they truly are a brilliant group.  Let's see, 4 singles released in
the UK, and four number ones...  One album released in the UK, and one
multi-platinum number one...  Number one album and single in the USA (always
a hard market to break into for foreign artists).  Perhaps brilliant is
a bit of an understatement :-)

Look at it another way.  I don't like wasting money on things, so the fact
that I've got both the singles AND the album must indicate that I really
do like them.  And since the last single I bought before Wannabe was over
five years ago, the fact that I have bought their singles proves something
as well.

But there must be more to it than that, I can hear some of you saying.  And yes,
you're quite right.  There's Melanie Chisholm...

That's right.  I'm rather fond of Mel C, if you define "rather fond of" as 
being "madly in love with".  Well, a man can dream, can't I!  And since I'm
so taken by her, I decided to set up the first 100% Mel C website.  Though there
are plenty of Spice Girls websites out there, all containing a variable
amount of Mel C stuff, there weren't any dedicated to JUST Mel C.  So, I
did the only decent thing and started my own.

                http://www.tornado.pair.com/mel_c/mel_c.html
                
If you're just a Spice Girls fan, you might be disappointed if you come and
visit.  On the other hand, if you're one of the growing number of Mel C
fans, I think you'll like my site.  Come take a look and see for yourself.
@endnode

@node "Program History" "Program History"
