5.  History

28.12.96  Several abortive attempts to start writing QuickCode, eventually
   to     ending with one version that seemed promising...
08.01.97

09.01.97  Final beta passes all checks...
12.01.97  V1.0 archive ready for release.
13.01.97  V1.1 update.  Nothing much, just removed a small and harmless warning 
          if you'd closed Mathscript before QuickCode.
14.01.97  Duuuh, in my eagerness to optimise the code, I removed a SELECT...END
          pair from QuickCode.rexx.  Oops!
          Duuuh Two, the Project...Quit menu option never actually did what it 
          said it would.  Oh dear :-)
17.01.97  Had a wierd bug report from Simon Ihmig, that seemed to show the 
          env-var losing entries...  I couldn't replicate the bug, even if I 
          followed his report step by step, although I once ended up with a 
          different bug that would give the same result!  So, although I have 
          NO idea what was going on, I've changed the code a bit so that the
          error I did see shouldn't happen ever again, and hopefully this'll
          also clear up the other problem...
          Oh yes, the Clear button now works again :-)
18.01.97  V1.2 update.  Adds the MxN matrix
21.01.97  V1.3 update.  Adds new codes from Mathscript 3.1, and rearranges the
          ones that got moved.
25.01.97  V1.4 update.  After more bug reports from Simon, I eventually managed
          to recreate the problem on my system, and I think it's now fixed!
          To make Quickcode run happily alongside other GUIs, all variable
          names have been altered to make them unique to Quickcode, and when
          Quickcode is closed, it leaves Gui4CLI in place.
28.01.97  V1.5 update.  I spoke too soon... but NOW I think that bug of Simon's
          is removed, once and for all!  (and now all I have to do is wait for
          Simon to email me again to say it isn't :-)
09.02.97  V1.6 update.  Simon emailed...to say the bug was fixed!
          Fixed a few other little bugs that I've just spotted, screen jumping
          really should be OK now.
          QuickCode now uses relative paths when searching for files, you no
          longer have to install it in the Mathscript:Rexx directory...
24.05.97  V1.7 update.  You can now turn the CLEAR button off, or add an
          "Are you sure?" requester, just in case.
          Changed website URL.
31.05.97  V1.8 update.  Bar position can now be saved.  The "Quit G4C on exit"
          option has been safeguarded, so that if there are other Guis active
          when QuickCode is closed, G4C will NOT be closed.


