@node "MathScript" "MathScript 3.1"
@next "Main"
@prev "Main"
Ah, a lost soul who downloaded this archive without reading the .readme...

QuickCode is an ARexx/Gui4CLI script for use with MathScript 3.1+, a rather 
nice WYSIWYG equation editor by Simon Ihmig.  Without it, QuickCode is really 
quite useless, unless you like collecting ARexx/Gui4CLI source, so I'd advise 
you to either go and get a copy of Mathscript, or delete this archive.  Of 
course, if this archive is sitting on a CDROM, deleting it is going to be 
difficult, so you have my permission to simply ignore it.  Thank you.


Mathscript can be obtained from Aminet, in misc/math.  The Mathscript
homepage can be found at:

                    http://www.mathscript.pair.com/


Remember, as of QuickCode 1.3 you need Mathscript 3.1+.  


@{"Return to Contents" link "Main" 0}
@endnode

@node "Distribution" "Distribution"
@next "Main"
@prev "Main"
This is the public release version of QuickCode, and may be distributed
freely provided no alterations of any kind are made to the archive.  With the
exception of the Aminet CD compilers, anyone wishing to use this archive on a
CD MUST contact me first.  Magazine coverdisk compilers must also contact me
if you want to use the archive.

I'm not interested in any form of payment, I'd just like to know where my
work ends up, and to make sure you've got the most up to date version
there is.

Anyone is free to alter the source code for their own use, but SHOULD NOT
distribute altered code without my permission.


NOTE:  The Gui and Gui4CLI executables are part of the @{"Gui4CLI" link "g4c" 0} 
package, copyright to Dimitris C. Keletsekis.  I have nothing whatsoever to do
with their creation or upkeep, and I include them in this archive with
the permission of Dimitris.
@endnode

